ABUJA  – Former Governor of Imo State, Senator Rochas Oko­rocha, on Monday, official­ly declared interest in the presidency in 2023. He pledged to surpass the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari in terms of uniting the entire country across religious and ethnic divides. Besides, the presidential aspirant also vowed that if allowed to become President, he would create an enabling environment for productive ventures to thrive, insisting that Nigeria was never in lack of resources but effective leaders that can manage the available resources. NiMET Warns Of Extreme Heats As Temperature Rises Across States Yobe Commends AFRYDEV For Training GBV Survivors The Senator representing Imo West Senatorial District in the 9th Senate, however, decried the high handedness within the ruling All Pro­gressives Congress (APC), claiming the party lacked justice and fairness, saying despite these shortcomings in the party, he would not back out because he and three other prominent politicians birthed what is today known as the APC. According to the Presi­dential aspirant, under his stewardship in 2023, Nigeria will no longer be tagged as the poverty capital of the world, insisting that having studied the peculiarities of Nigeria, he can galvanise human and material resources to uplift the country.